The #1 mistake on the military press is not pushing your elbows forward enough in the bottom of the movement. 

Old Russian training manuals describe the initial motion of the press as an "enthusiastic upward drive of the elbow" - and for Russians to use the word enthusiastic is really saying something!

To achieve this you need to do a few things:

1️⃣ Depress your shoulder blades (down, not together) and flex your lats. 

2️⃣ Push your elbows forward so they're directly under the bar, or even a touch in front of it. 

3️⃣ Start the press by driving your elbows straight up until the bar is about eyebrow level. 

4️⃣ As you pass your eyebrows you start spreading your elbows apart as you continue to press. 

5️⃣ To get back to the right start position you want to think about taking the weight down with your lats as your elbows come down and then back into the start position.

Ever wondered why elite Strongman athletes like Trey Mitchell swear by wearing the Ursus during their training? 🤔 Let’s break it down:

👣 Unleash Your Feet - Traditional shoes with thick soles can create a barrier between you and the ground. Bearfoot Shoes strip away the excess, allowing your feet to engage directly with the floor, boosting stability and proprioception.

🔥 Amplify Your Form - Bearfoot Shoes encourage a more natural foot position, helping you maintain proper posture during lifts. This means more effective, safer training sessions and fewer chances of injury.

💪🏼 Strengthen Key Muscles-  Flat, flexible soles allow you activate a network of smaller muscles in your feet and lower legs. This added challenge translates to improved balance, stability, and overall strength gains.

Join the Bearfoot movement; Train like a champion, conquer your goals, and redefine your limits 🐻👣
